HEADWORD: Quadragene
<hw>Quad"ra*gene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>quadragena</ets>, fr. L. <ets>quadrageni</ets> forty each, akin to
<ets>quadraginta</ets> forty.]</ety> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>An
indulgence of forty days, corresponding to the forty days of ancient
canonical penance.</def>⟦br⟧
